    "en": "CI/CD: Automate Everything",
    "ta": "CI/CD: எல்லாவற்றையும் தானியங்கு செய்யுங்கள்"
  },
  "description": {
    "en": "Understand Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery. Learn how GitHub Actions automates testing, linting, and deployment on every push.",
    "ta": "Continuous Integration மற்றும் Continuous Delivery புரிந்துகொள்ளுங்கள். GitHub Actions எவ்வாறு ஒவ்வொரு push-லும் testing, linting, deployment தானியங்கு செய்கிறது என்பதை கற்றுக்கொள்ளுங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 55,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Assembly Line\n\nVaathiyaar draws a factory on the whiteboard. \"Imagine a car factory. Raw materials go in one end. At each station, something happens automatically — welding, painting, inspection, packaging. The car rolls off the line ready to ship. That's CI/CD for software.\"\n\n### What is CI/CD?\n- **CI (Continuous Integration)** — Every code push triggers automated tests\n- **CD (Continuous Delivery)** — Code that passes tests is automatically prepared for release\n- **CD (Continuous Deployment)** — Code is automatically deployed to production\n\n### Why CI/CD?\n- Catch bugs immediately, not days later\n- Every commit is tested — no \"it works on my machine\"\n- Deploy with confidence, not anxiety\n- Small, frequent releases beat big, scary ones\n\n### GitHub Actions\n- Built into GitHub — no extra service needed\n- Triggered by events: push, pull_request, schedule\n- Defined in YAML files: `.github/workflows/`\n- Free for public repos, generous free tier for private\n\n> **Key Concept:** CI/CD turns manual, error-prone steps into an automated pipeline. If you push code, the robots do the rest — test, build, deploy."
  },
